The paper deals with signal recovery from compressive linear measurements, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of Gaussian mixture models and expectation maximization suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) approach. The use of approximate message passing (AMP) is a numerical analysis (cs.NA) technique.
